he RNGs verification function\n   350→\n   351→**Item**: Phase C, item 2 — Add verification function to game-engine\n   352→\n   353→**What was done**:\n   354→- Added to `packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`:\n   355→  - `RoundSettledEvent` interface — typed representation of the on-chain RoundSettled event fields (tier, roundNumber, winner, randomness, winningSlot, totalEntries, payoutAmount, feeAmount, vrfRequestKey)\n   356→  - `LordVerificationResult` interface — verification result with valid flag, error messages, and computed values\n   357→  - `verifyLordRound(event, players)` — re-derives winning slot from VRF randomness using `determineWinnerFromRandomness`, verifies it matches event's claimed slot and winner, also checks fee = 3% of total pool\n   358→  - `calculateJackpotPayout(tier, totalEntries)` — computes winner payout (pool × 0.97), mirrors coinflip's `calculatePotentialPayout` but for N-player jackpot\n   359→- Updated `packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`:\n   360→  - Added exports: `verifyLordRound`, `calculateJackpotPayout`, `RoundSettledEvent`, `LordVerificationResult`\n   361→- Design decision: verification lives in game-engine (not fairness package) because fairness package is HMAC/crash-specific while VRF verification uses `@solana/web3.js` types (PublicKey)\n   362→\n   363→**Verification**: `pnpm typecheck` — 17/17 packages pass. `pnpm lint` — 17/17 packages pass (0 errors).\n   364→\n   365→**Status**: Done\n   366→\n   367→## Iteration 12 — 2026-02-26T23:10:00Z — OK\n   368→- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   369→\n   370→## Iteration 12 — 2026-02-26T23:09:27Z — OK\n   371→- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   372→\n   373→## Iteration 13 — Sync lordofrngs IDL to anchor-client package\n   374→\n   375→**Item**: Phase C, item 3 — Sync IDL and export typed program interface\n   376→\n   377→**What was done**:\n   378→- Ran `anchor build -p lordofrngs` — confirmed IDL at `solana/target/idl/lordofrngs.json` and types at `solana/target/types/lordofrngs.ts` are up to date\n   379→- Ran `./scripts/sync-idl` — copied `lordofrngs.json` and `lordofrngs.ts` to `packages/anchor-client/src/`\n   380→- Updated `packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`:\n   381→  - Added `import LordofrngsIDL from \"./lordofrngs.json\" with { type: \"json\" }`\n   382→  - Added `export type { Lordofrngs } from \"./lordofrngs.js\"`\n   383→  - Added `LordofrngsIDL` to re-exports\n   384→- Consumers can now import: `import { LordofrngsIDL, type Lordofrngs } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\"`\n   385→\n   386→**Verification**:\n   387→- `anchor build -p lordofrngs` — passed\n   388→- `pnpm typecheck` — 17/17 packages pass\n   389→- `pnpm lint` — 17/17 packages pass (0 errors)\n   390→- `pnpm build` (platform) — passed\n   391→- Note: `pnpm build:all` (turbo) fails on non-platform scaffold apps missing `index.html` — pre-existing issue, not related to this change\n   392→\n   393→**Status**: Done\n   394→\n   395→## Iteration 13 — 2026-02-26T23:14:17Z — OK\n   396→- **Log**: iteration-013.log\n   397→\n   398→## Iteration 14 — Create chain.ts for Lord of the RNGs frontend\n   399→\n   400→**Item**: Phase D, item 1 — Create `features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts`\n   401→\n   402→**What was done**:\n   403→- Created `apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts`:\n   404→  - **Program Setup**: `getLordProgram()` — read-only Anchor program instance, `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID` from env or IDL\n   405→  - **PDA Derivation**: `getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber)`, `getConfigPda()`, `getOraoNetworkStatePda()`, `getOraoRandomnessPda(seed)`\n   406→  - **On-Chain Types**: `OnChainRound`, `OnChainPlayerEntry`, `OnChainConfig` — typed interfaces for deserialized accounts\n   407→  - **Converters**: `onChainRoundToUI(pda, data, wallet)` — converts on-chain JackpotRound to frontend Round type; `onChainPlayersToUI()` — converts player entries with color assignment; `phaseToUI()` — maps on-chain phases (Waiting/Active/Locked/Settled) to UI phases (waiting/countdown/spinning/complete)\n   408→  - **VRF Helpers**: `readVrfRandomness()` — reads 32 bytes from Orao randomness account; `deriveWinnerFromVrf()` — client-side winner derivation matching on-chain logic\n   409→  - **Account Queries**: `fetchRound(connection, tier, roundNumber)` — single round fetch; `fetchAllTierRounds(connection)` — fetches latest active round per tier; `fetchClaimableRounds(connection, playerPubkey)` — finds rounds with fulfilled VRF where player participated\n   410→  - **Transaction Builders**: `buildJoinRoundTx()`, `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx()`, `buildStartSpinTx()`, `buildClaimPayoutTx()`, `buildCreateRoundTx()` — all follow coinflip chain.ts pattern (derive PDAs, build instruction via Anchor methods, create unsigned Transaction)\n   411→- Mirrors coinflip `chain.ts` architecture: read-only program instance, `accountsStrict` for all instructions, BigInt for u64 args, Orao VRF treasury fetched from network state\n   412→\n   413→**Verification**: `pnpm typecheck` — 17/17 packages pass. `pnpm lint` — 17/17 packages pass (0 errors).\n   414→\n   415→**Status**: Done\n   416→\n   417→\n   418→## Iteration 14 — 2026-02-26T23:18:49Z — OK\n   419→- **Log**: iteration-014.log\n   420→\n   421→## Iteration 15 — Update LordOfRngsContext.tsx with on-chain calls\n   422→\n   423→**Item**: Phase D, item 2 — Update `LordOfRngsContext.tsx` to use chain.ts\n   424→\n   425→**What was done**:\n   426→- Rewrote `LordOfRngsContext.tsx` to replace all mock-simulation imports with real on-chain calls via chain.ts:\n   427→  - **Imports**: Replaced mock-simulation functions with chain.ts exports (`fetchAllTierRounds`, `fetchRound`, `buildCreateRoundTx`, `buildJoinRoundTx`, `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx`, `buildStartSpinTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`, `getLordProgram`, `getConfigPda`)\n   428→  - **Wallet hooks**: Added `useWallet` (publicKey, sendTransaction), `useConnection`, `useBalance` — same pattern as CoinflipContext\n   429→  - **`sendAndConfirm` helper**: Fresh blockhash → sendTransaction → confirmTransaction → refreshBalance\n   430→  - **`joinTierRound`**: Fetches tier rounds, creates new round via `buildCreateRoundTx` if none exists, or joins via `buildJoinRoundTx`. Stores `activeRoundMeta` (tierIndex + roundNumber) for subsequent tx building\n   431→  - **`buyMoreEntriesAction`**: Builds tx via `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx`, sends, refreshes round\n   432→  - **`startSpin`**: New action — builds tx via `buildStartSpinTx`, sends, transitions to \"spinning\" phase\n   433→  - **`claimPayout`**: Builds tx via `buildClaimPayoutTx`, sends, auto-transitions back to lobby\n   434→  - **`handleAutoClaim`**: Auto-triggered when polling detects VRF fulfilled and player is winner\n   435→  - **Polling**: 5s interval when in active round (polls `fetchRound`), 15s for lobby (`fetchAllTierRounds`)\n   436→  - **Error handling**: `parseTransactionError()` helper maps wallet/program errors to user-friendly messages\n   437→  - **New context fields**: `spinning`, `startSpin`, `error`, `clearError` (additive — no breaking changes to existing consumers)\n   438→- Exported `getLordProgram` from chain.ts (was previously private)\n   439→- Added `fetchRoundNumberForTier()` helper to derive round number from on-chain config\n   440→\n   441→**Verification**: `pnpm typecheck` — 17/17 packages pass. `pnpm lint` — 17/17 packages pass (0 errors, 43 pre-existing warnings).\n   442→\n   443→**Status**: Done\n   444→\n   445→## Iteration 15 — 2026-02-26T23:25:28Z — OK\n   446→- **Log**: iteration-015.log\n   447→\n   448→## Iteration 16 — Update tier types to use SOL amounts\n   449→\n   450→**Item**: Phase D, item 3 — Update tier types to use SOL amounts\n   451→\n   452→**What was done**:\n   453→- Updated `types.ts`:\n   454→  - Changed `entryAmount` comment from `// Cost per entry in $` to `// Cost per entry in SOL`\n   455→  - Changed `poolAmount` comment from `// Total $ in pool` to `// Total SOL in pool`\n   456→- Updated `TierLobby.tsx`:\n   457→  - Ch