{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UkSsrG5qjBLFQUz1KFnuqY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 002 Crash (Crypto Crash Simulator)\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Draft |\n     8→| Ideation | Active |\n     9→| Priority | P1 |\n    10→| Phase | Deferred |\n    11→| NR_OF_TRIES | 0 |\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→## Overview\n    16→\n    17→Crash is a competitive P2P multiplayer game where players watch a multiplier climb from 1.00x and must cash out before it crashes. Within each betting tier, the player with the highest valid cashout wins that tier's entire pool. Rounds run in a continuous loop of betting, running, crashed, and winner reveal phases. This game is planned after the first two V1 games (Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs).\n    18→\n    19→## User Stories\n    20→\n    21→- As a player, I want to select a tier and place a bet during the betting phase so that I can enter the next crash round at stakes I choose.\n    22→- As a player, I want to watch a multiplier climb in real-time so that I can decide when to cash out.\n    23→- As a player, I want to cash out at the right moment so that I can beat other players in my tier and win the pool.\n    24→- As a player, I want to see who won each tier after a crash so that I know the results and my payout.\n    25→- As a player, I want to verify that the crash point was determined fairly before the round began so that I trust the game.\n    26→- As a player, I want to see jackpot carryovers from previous rounds so that I'm attracted to tiers with larger pools.\n    27→\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→## Scope Alignment\n    31→\n    32→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 12 (Post-Launch Expansion - Additional game(s))\n    33→- **Scope status**: Deferred (P2P multiplayer mode only; Classic house mode deferred)\n    34→- **Phase boundary**: Post-V1\n    35→\n    36→## Required Context Files\n    37→\n    38→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/CRASH.md` (game concept source)\n    39→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, provably fair system)\n    40→- `docs/SCOPE.md` (scope boundary, shared game requirements)\n    41→\n    42→## Contract Files\n    43→\n    44→- [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] Frontend mock/component files for Crash UI\n    45→- [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] On-chain program interface for pool manager + VRF consumer\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## Functional Requirements\n    50→\n    51→### FR-1: Betting Phase\n    52→\n    53→Players have a 20-second window to select a tier and place their wager. One bet per player per round.\n    54→\n    55→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    56→- [ ] 20-second countdown timer displayed with audio cues at 3, 2, 1 seconds\n    57→- [ ] Player can select one of six tiers (Iron through Diamond)\n    58→- [ ] Live player count and pool size shown per tier\n    59→- [ ] Tier selection is locked once bet is placed\n    60→- [ ] One bet per player per round\n    61→- [ ] Bet requires connected wallet with sufficient balance\n    62→\n    63→### FR-2: Running Phase (Multiplier Climb)\n    64→\n    65→The multiplier starts at 1.00x and climbs. Players can cash out at any moment. The visual shows green candles rising.\n    66→\n    67→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    68→- [ ] Multiplier starts at 1.00x and climbs using formula: multiplier = 1.12 ^ elapsed_seconds\n    69→- [ ] Multiplier rounded down to 2 decimal places for display\n    70→- [ ] Maximum multiplier capped at 100.00x\n    71→- [ ] Player can click \"CASH OUT\" at any moment during this phase\n    72→- [ ] Cash out is irreversible; multiplier is locked in immediately\n    73→- [ ] Current potential payout displayed to player\n    74→- [ ] List of recent cashouts from other players visible\n    75→- [ ] Smooth animation targeting 60fps\n    76→\n    77→### FR-3: Crash Point Determination\n    78→\n    79→Crash points use VRF seed + commit-reveal (per `docs/pivot-doc.md` §4 and `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`). VRF is requested during the waiting/lobby phase — the output becomes the seed. The server runs the engine off-chain and proves results via commit-reveal.\n    80→\n    81→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    82→- [ ] VRF seed requested pre-round during WAITING phase (latency absorbed before gameplay)\n    83→- [ ] Crash point derived deterministically from VRF seed\n    84→- [ ] Server commits `SHA256(server_seed)` before round starts\n    85→- [ ] Server reveals `server_seed` at settlement; contract verifies `SHA256(server_seed) == stored_hash`\n    86→- [ ] Same VRF seed always produces same crash point (deterministic)\n    87→- [ ] Crash distribution balanced for P2P mode (frequent high multipliers)\n    88→- [ ] Small percentage of instant crashes (1.00x) for tension\n    89→- [ ] 20% of rounds receive a boost (1.5x to 3.0x multiplier on base crash point)\n    90→- [ ] Boost factor deterministically derived from VRF output\n    91→\n    92→### FR-4: Crashed Phase\n    93→\n    94→When the multiplier reaches the crash point, the game crashes. Players who did not cash out lose their bets to the tier pool.\n    95→\n    96→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    97→- [ ] Crash visual: large red dump candle (crypto pump-and-dump aesthetic)\n    98→- [ ] Final crash multiplier displayed prominently in red\n    99→- [ ] \"CRASHED\" text displayed\n   100→- [ ] Crash sound effect plays\n   101→- [ ] Bets from players who didn't cash out go into winner's prize pool\n   102→- [ ] Phase lasts approximately 3 seconds\n   103→\n   104→### FR-5: Winner Reveal Phase\n   105→\n   106→Per-tier winners are announced. The winner is the player with the highest valid cashout multiplier in each tier.\n   107→\n   108→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   109→- [ ] Winner = player with highest cashout multiplier that is <= crash point\n   110→- [ ] Up to six winners per round (one per active tier)\n   111→- [ ] Winner card shows: avatar, name, cashout multiplier, payout amount\n   112→- [ ] \"You Won!\" celebration if current player won\n   113→- [ ] \"No Winner\" displayed if nobody in a tier cashed out\n   114→- [ ] Countdown to next round shown\n   115→- [ ] Phase lasts approximately 3 seconds\n   116→\n   117→### FR-6: Settlement and Payout\n   118→\n   119→Winner of each tier receives that tier's pool minus the platform fee.\n   120→\n   121→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   122→- [ ] Winner payout = tier_pool x 0.97 (3% platform fee)\n   123→- [ ] Platform fee collected to treasury PDA\n   124→- [ ] Settlement recorded on-chain\n   125→- [ ] Settlement is idempotent\n   126→- [ ] Replay protection for signed actions\n   127→\n   128→### FR-7: Prize Pool Carryover\n   129→\n   130→If no player in a tier cashes out successfully, the pool carries over to the next round.\n   131→\n   132→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   133→- [ ] Carryover = tier_pool x 0.97 (fee still deducted)\n   134→- [ ] Carryover pools accumulate until someone wins\n   135→- [ ] Carryover amount displayed prominently: \"JACKPOT: X SOL\"\n   136→- [ ] Pulsing/glowing effect on tier selection for carryover tiers\n   137→\n   138→### FR-8: Fairness Verification\n   139→\n   140→Players can verify crash points and commit-reveal proofs for any completed round.\n   141→\n   142→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   143→- [ ] VRF proof is publicly viewable for the round's seed\n   144→- [ ] Revealed `server_seed` and stored commitment hash are publicly viewable\n   145→- [ ] Players can verify `SHA256(server_seed) == commitment_hash`\n   146→- [ ] Players can recalculate crash point from VRF seed\n   147→- [ ] Verification accessible from round history and result screen\n   148→- [ ] Boost factor verifiable from VRF output\n   149→\n   150→### FR-9: Betting Phase UI\n   151→\n   152→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   153→- [ ] Prominent 20-second countdown timer\n   154→- [ ] Tier selection grid showing all six tiers\n   155→- [ ] Live player count and pool size per tier\n   156→- [ ] Clear \"Place Bet\" button with tier amount\n   157→- [ ] Disable tier selection after bet placed\n   158→\n   159→### FR-10: Running Phase UI\n   160→\n   161→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   162→- [ ] Large animated multiplier display (center screen)\n   163→- [ ] Green candles rising to represent growth\n   164→- [ ] Prominent \"CASH OUT\" button\n   165→- [ ] Current potential payout displayed\n   166→- [ ] Recent cashouts from other players listed\n   167→\n   168→### FR-11: Audio Feedback\n   169→\n   170→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   171→- [ ] Countdown beeps at 3, 2, 1 seconds during betting phase\n   172→- [ ] Rising tension audio during running phase\n   173→- [ ] Crash/dump sound effect on crash\n   174→- [ ] Cash-out confirmation sound on successful cashout\n   175→- [ ] Victory fanfare for winners\n   176→\n   177→---\n   178→\n   179→## Success Criteria\n   180→\n   181→- A player can place a bet, watch the multiplier climb, cash out, and receive payout in a continuous round loop\n   182→- Settlement correctness: tier winner always receives exactly (tier_pool x 0.97), fee always reaches treasury\n   183→- Carryover pools accumulate correctly and pay out when a winner exists\n   184→- Any round's crash point can be independently verified\n   185→- Round loop runs continuously without manual intervention\n   186→- Cash-out timing is fair: server is authoritative for cash-out registration\n   187→\n   188→---\n   189→\n   190→## Dependencies\n   191→\n   192→- Wallet connection (PLAT-004) must be functional\n   193→- Shared infrastructure spec (`docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`) — lifecycle, escrow, commit-reveal, fees\n   194→- VRF provider selected (per 004 spec FR-4)\n   195→- Shared UI components (PLAT-003)\n   196→- Game engine package (PLAT-005) for round state machine\n   197→- Real-time state sync infrastructure [NEEDS CLARIFICATION - WebSocket vs polling decision pending]\n   198→- Coinflip (001) validates core settlement + fairness flows first\n   199→\n   200→## Assumptions\n   201→\n   202→- P2P multiplayer mode only for V1 (Classic house mode deferred)\n   203→- Platform fee is 3% (300 bps). Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §8. Split: 200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest treasury.\n   204→- Crash uses VRF seed + commit-reveal (not HMAC-only). See `docs/pivot-doc.md` §4.\n   205→- Real-time sync approach will be decided before implementation\n   206→- Boost mechanic (20% of rounds) is included in V1\n   207→\n   208→---\n   209→\n   210→## Validation Plan\n   211→\n   212→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   213→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   214→| 1 | Betting phase accepts bets within timer | Place bet, verify acceptance | Screenshot of bet confirmation |\n   215→| 2 | Multiplier climbs per formula | Record multiplier over time, verify formula | Time-series data or video |\n   216→| 3 | Cash out locks in multiplier | Cash out, verify locked value | Screenshot of locked multiplier |\n   217→| 4 | Crash point is deterministic | Run same round number twice, verify same result | Two results with matching crash points |\n   218→| 5 | Winner = highest valid cashout | Multi-player round, verify winner selection | Round results showing all cashouts |\n   219→| 6 | Carryover works on no-winner round | Trigger no-cashout round, verify carryover | Next round showing accumulated pool |\n   220→| 7 | Payout = tier_pool x 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement | Explorer link showing amounts |\n   221→| 8 | Fairness verification | Recalculate crash point from public inputs | Verification UI screenshot |\n   222→| 9 | Boost mechanic applies correctly | Verify boosted round vs base crash point | Hash + boost factor calculation |\n   223→| 10 | Continuous round loop | Observe 5+ consecutive rounds | Video or log of round transitions |\n   224→\n   225→---\n   226→\n   227→## Completion Signal\n   228→\n   229→### Implementation Checklist\n   230→- [ ] Betting phase (timer, tier selection, bet placement)\n   231→- [ ] Running phase (multiplier engine, cash-out handling)\n   232→- [ ] Crash point generation (VRF seed + commit-reveal + boost mechanic)\n   233→- [ ] Crashed phase (visual, state transition)\n   234→- [ ] Winner determination (per-tier highest valid cashout)\n   235→- [ ] Settlement flow (on-chain payout recording)\n   236→- [ ] Carryover logic (no-winner pool accumulation)\n   237→- [ ] Fairness verification UI\n   238→- [ ] All phase UI components (betting, running, crashed, winner reveal)\n   239→- [ ] Audio integration\n   240→- [ ] Real-time state sync\n   241→- [ ] Continuous round loop\n   242→- [ ] Error states and recovery paths\n   243→- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   244→- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   245→- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is in scope, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   246→\n   247→### Testing Requirements\n   248→\n   249→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   250→\n   251→#### Code Quality\n   252→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   253→- [ ] New tests for multiplier formula and crash point generation\n   254→- [ ] New tests for winner determination logic\n   255→- [ ] New tests for carryover calculations\n   256→- [ ] No lint errors\n   257→\n   258→#### Functional Verification\n   259→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   260→- [ ] Edge cases: all players crash out, single player in tier, max multiplier reached, boost boundary\n   261→- [ ] Idempotency verified for settlement\n   262→- [ ] Replay protection verified\n   263→\n   264→#### Visual Verification\n   265→- [ ] All four phase UIs render correctly on desktop\n   266→- [ ] Multiplier animation smooth at target framerate\n   267→- [ ] Mobile responsive layout works\n   268→\n   269→#### Console/Network Check\n   270→- [ ] No JS console errors during continuous round play\n   271→- [ ] No failed network requests\n   272→- [ ] On-chain transactions succeed on devnet\n   273→\n   274→### Iteration Instructions\n   275→\n   276→If ANY check fails:\n   277→1. Identify the specific issue\n   278→2. Fix the code\n   279→3. Re-run tests\n   280→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   281→5. Check again\n   282→\n   283→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   284→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PRSLefhQeBwpvqapfE6EQp","session_id":"e8e7bcc0-e29f-4246-996e-49dc6d7211e9","uuid":"8fb158ac-ed0a-4c33-8123-aca1221ffaf2"}
